<darktable_style version="1.0"><info><name>denoise</name><description>Parameterized denoising via darktable's denoiseprofile module (#96). Non-local-means (NLMEANS) denoising with 4 magnitude axes: --param strength=V (range [0.001, 1000.0]; primary noise slider), --param shadows=V (range [0.0, 1.8]; preserve shadow noise vs detail), --param radius=V (range [0.0, 12.0]; patch size), --param scattering=V (range [0.0, 20.0]; search-zone spread). Per-channel noise calibration a[3]/b[3] is auto-populated by darktable when the camera+ISO is in its profile database. NOTE: the wavelet curve baseline (x[6][7] / y[6][7]) is constructed, not empirically captured — see #96 closing notes and the darktable-session verification follow-up.</description></info><style><plugin><num>0</num><module>12</module><operation>denoiseprofile</operation><op_params></op_params><enabled>1</enabled><blendop_params>gz11eJxjYIAACQYYOOHEgAZY0QWAgBGLGANDgz0Ej1Q+dcF/IADRAGpyHQU=</blendop_params><blendop_version>14</blendop_version><multi_priority>0</multi_priority><multi_name></multi_name><multi_name_hand_edited>0</multi_name_hand_edited></plugin></style></darktable_style>
